snippet.textDisplay: When I was younger, I wanted to try every hot sauce there was and the hotter the better. I'd put hot sauce on everything. Then one night, I was eating hot shrimp with scoville around 250,000 and it hit me...I may as well forget the shrimp because the hot sauce overpowered everything. I realized, I wanted hot sauce, but I also wanted flavor. Then I settled on standard Crystal. It has heat and flavor that compliments what you are eating. Going off the scale, especially if you are paying for the food in a restaurant,  is stupid IMO. Other than trying to impress someone, what do you gain by eating the hottest sauce, other than pain going in and worse pain coming out? However, I guess there are people who crave and need that heat. This host probably being one of them. Oh and yes, Margot Robbie is way too hot without the sauce.
